horse show help on tuesday july i purchased an year old thoroughbred to be used for hunter jumper i have a show on august it is only a small schooling show but i dont have a ton of time to work with him before the big day please give me some tips on what to do to stay calm and to place the show is at my barn have all your supplies ready in advance so you don't have to get anything last minute have a couple practice sessions where you get your horse all ready as if you are at the show and time yourself so you know how long you need in advance find a quiet place where you can mentally picture your class in your mind before you go in the ring this helps you focus and stay calm breathe in breathe out sink deep into your heels and feel yourself get very relaxed in the saddle think about happy things and nice places these are things that have helped me stuff my walls with ribbons and trophies over the years Equine conformation Jon Secada Tai Chi Chuan Shaggy dog story Thoroughbred Show jumping Obedience training Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Insomnia Show hunter Care Bears Horse EastEnders Anapana 2000 Australian Grand Prix Current teachings of Prem Rawat Thoroughbred horse race The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Psychoanalysis Marching band The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Eventing The Amazing Race Past teachings of Prem Rawat Tina Turner Parachuting Eddie Guerrero Massage Wassily Kandinsky Montreal Screwjob Backstroke Submarine Time Out of Mind Glen Jacobs Meditation Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Sonic the Hedgehog Horse breaking Chris Jericho The Ashlee Simpson Show Fire fighting Arabian horse American Quarter Horse Vipassana Belmont Park Milton H. Erickson Cruising (maritime) The Book of Five Rings Aristotle Frankie Laine Social rule Hunt seat AFI 100 Years series American Saddlebred Theory of conduct Equitation Mission UK Lucid dreaming Horse show The Adventures of Pete & Pete USS Sealion (SS-315) 2005 trial of Michael Jackson USS Tunny (SS-282) West Brom